{
  "texts": [
    "For rating generative models and identifying their flaws, effective assessment metrics are crucial and require exploring.",
    "• It is not yet known how much training data is memorized by generative models.",
    "A Well-known method \"use of nearest neighbors\" is a frequent method of testing memory which suffer from number of flaws that require to optimize.",
    "• It has been discovered from evidence that implies evaluation parameters like IS or FID as a loss function can enhance the samples of a generator; however, when this happens and when it does not remain unclear and should be the focus of future study.",
    "• More study is needed to fill the gap in faked image analysis caused by the three primary technical obstacles encountered during training of GANs: mode collapse, non-convergence, and instability."
  ]
}